The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a press release on September 16, 2011, providing a summary of a press gaggle with Press Secretary Jay Carney and Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications Ben Rhodes. The gaggle previewed the United Nations General Assembly and discussed President Obama's schedule for the week. The President would have a busy week with meetings and events related to Libya, Afghanistan, Brazil, Turkey, South Sudan, and other issues. The gaggle also touched on the Israeli-Palestinian issue, the possibility of a double-dip recession, and the emails regarding Solyndra. The press release did not provide detailed summaries of each topic discussed, but rather offered a general overview of the topics covered during the press gaggle.